      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: convert reasoning_content to thinking blocks for All OpenAI-compatible providers",
        "body": "\r\n## Problem\r\nModels like Xiaomi MiMo (and other OpenAI-compatible providers) return `reasoning_content` in their response stream. The gateway was silently dropping this field, causing loss of reasoning/thinking data.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, as noted in #83402, MiMo models reject the cron embedded agent tool schema with a 400 Param Incorrect error, the tool payload schema is not compatible with Xiaomi's implementation.\r\n\r\n## Fix\r\nParse `reasoning_content` from the streaming delta and emit it as a proper thinking block with `thinkingSignature: \"reasoning_content\"`, matching the format used by Anthropic and other native providers.\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n* **[src/gateway/openai-http.ts](src/gateway/openai-http.ts)**: Added `reasoning_content` $\\rightarrow$ thinking block conversion in the streaming delta parser.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\nVerified locally with `mimo-v2.5` , `mimo-v2.5-pro` model, reasoning content now appears correctly in session logs without errors.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n> **Note**: This fix enables proper handling of reasoning/thinking data from OpenAI-compatible models that expose reasoning through `reasoning_content`, improving transparency and debugging capabilities.",
